Prove 0 ≤ i < n + 1  ≡  0 ≤ i < n ⋁ i = n

  0 ≤ i < n + 1
=    〈 Remove the conjunctive abbreviation 〉
  0 ≤ i ⋀ i < n + 1
=    〈 i < n + 1  ≡  i < n ⋁ i = n 〉
  0 ≤ i ⋀ (i < n ⋁ i = n)
=    〈 (3.46) Distributivity of ⋀ over ⋁ 〉
  (0 ≤ i ⋀ i < n) ⋁ (0 ≤ i ⋀ i = n)
=    〈 (3.84a) Substitution 〉
  (0 ≤ i ⋀ i < n) ⋁ (0 ≤ n ⋀ i = n)
=    〈 Assume 0 ≤ n 〉
  (0 ≤ i ⋀ i < n) ⋁ (true ⋀ i = n)
=    〈 (3.39) Identity of ⋀ 〉
  (0 ≤ i ⋀ i < n) ⋁ i = n
=    〈 Reintroduce the conjunctive meaning 〉
  0 ≤ i < n  ⋁  i = n ╱╱
